bio.experienceSummary:
Hello, I'm a former teacher and mom of 4 children who are now ages 19-25. I'm Math teacher by education and training. I speak both English and Russian. 
I'm mature, caring, patient, attentive, engaging, experienced in infant/ child care and education. I'm reliable and punctual. I've been assisting families with infants and young children in Bayonne, Jersey City, Hoboken, Weehawken, NYC. I love to read to the children, engage them in fun and educational activities. I will create safe environment for your child. I also enjoy taking kids to the park/ playground ( weather/ CDC guidelines permit).
I'm up to date with Flu, Pneumonia, TDaP vaccinations.
I'm fully vaccinated and boosted.
By all means I welcome background check.

description.originalText:
Whatever I write here will not do Svetlana justice. She was flexible and endlessly kind and she helped us make our weekend trip a resounding success. She walked in and my nephew was almost immediately at ease. He had such a good time with Svetlana singing and drawing together. She certainly left an impression as he was asking about her after we'd left town. 

Anyway, I can't really say enough good things. Thank you Svetlana for taking care of our little guy.

bio.experienceSummary:
I'm passionate about fostering the growth and development of children. With over four years of experience, I'm skilled at caring for kids of all ages, from infants to preteens. My patient and calm demeanor, coupled with my creativity and imagination, allows me to connect with children and make learning fun.

I believe in open communication with parents and regularly provide written daily reports and updates via text or phone call, whichever you prefer. I prioritize following your lead when it comes to enforcing household rules and am comfortable caring for up to two children at a time.

From outdoor sports to educational games and technology-based apps, I love engaging children in a variety of activities that promote physical, mental, and emotional development. My experience includes caring for my brother since he was a baby and I have a2-year-old son of my own. I'm excited to bring my passion and expertise to your family!

description.originalText: Arianna is an amazing individual. She was very patient with my daughter. Her communication skills were excellent, I felt more than safe leaving my little girl with her!

bio.experienceSummary:
I'd describe my personality as respectful, kind and lovely person

I like working with children and seniors because I always love to help them. As a child I care of them as they are my family.

I specially love to care infants or toddlers because first Is true that parents need support and second because they are so sweet. Since I am with my couple we try to have one but unfortunately we can't so caring babies is like come true my dream.

I have experience improving their skills, napping time, changing diapers and making bottles. 

It is so proud to see how kid start to grow and understand the things. It is an amazing experience 

I would love to work with you

I've been a childcare provider for 12 years because I'm passionate about nurturing children's development. I'm patient, creative, and formal. I keep parents informed about their child's day and address any issues that arise through written daily reports, verbal communication, and regular updates. While I prefer a relaxed approach, I'm comfortable enforcing household rules when necessary. I enjoy a variety of games with children, from educational to technology-based. I'm comfortable caring for up to four children, and I have experience with children of all ages. My graduate degree and Spanish fluency further enhance my ability to provide a well-rounded and nurturing environment for the children in my care.

I am a 39-year-old mother of one wonderful 14-year-old girl now a 9th grader and she is the love of my life! I have over 13+ years of experience as a nanny. I can provide excellent verifiable reference available. I am seeking work ideally in Brooklyn and Staten Island, Manhattan. I am a hands on individual who enjoys arts and crafts, singing, reading and above all playing with children. I take care of all the light housekeeping duties pertaining to the children as well. I can run any errands you might need done, groceries, laundry and clean up the nursery/room. I have several reliable transportation options. Most importantly I will treat and care for your children as if they were my own. Their safety and well being is of utmost importance to me. CPR and first aide certified. I enjoy the outdoors and recreation.

description.originalText: We had a trial run with Erika and she was excellent. The moment she stepped in, she was professional and definitely showed a high standard of care.

bio.experienceSummary:
My goal as a Nanny is to care for, guide, instruct, protect, and teach children. I have more them 25years experience, I am willing to do
housekeeping that includes helping children clean their rooms, clean play area, and laundry. If I had to describe myself in five adjectives I would say that I am caring, loving, committed, responsible, and diligent.

description.originalText: Andreia has worked with my family for many years and is a wonderful person and babysitter. She’s helped care for my daughter and twin boys since they were toddlers. She is trustworthy, reliable and a hard worker! I can’t recommend Andreia enough and hope she finds a new family to grow with.

bio.experienceSummary:
EXPERIENCED Nanny available for weekends (Friday, Saturday, Sunday). I'm not looking for a steady weekend job, just an "as needed" job.

Mature, responsible, nurturing, flexible, creative and reliable! I have worked with children from 3 months to 16 years old. 

About me: I am a mom to one daughter whom I've raised on my own (her dad/my husband passed away in 2008). She is 25 now. I am a college graduate and worked for 9 years as a paraprofessional (aide for special needs children) with Westfield Board of Education. I've been a full time nanny for 8 years but a before school care and after school care nanny for over 10 years.

bio.experienceSummary: Hi there! My name is Madeline, I am 26 years old and am currently a full-time student during the day and have been working with children ranging from 6 months through 12 years old, as well as adults with physical disabilities. I have a background in healthcare and am CPR certified, I am available during the week any time after 5 p.m.  with occasional earlier availability depending on my class schedule. I love board games, cooking, and gardening!

Hi there! My name is Yaira, and I'm thrilled to meet you. I'm bilingual (English and Spanish) and a proud Colombian. I'm 23 years old and have over 1400 hours of experience in childcare. Before becoming an au pair, I worked as a volunteer at a daycare for a whole year. I'm certified in CPR and can swim like a pro. I also have a degree in Social Communication. I don't smoke or drink alcohol. 

I live in New Jersey and am great at adapting to new places. I love connecting with families and making a positive impact on children's lives. I'm excited to chat with you and see if we can work together!

description.originalText:
Yaira is with us 3-4 days a week, and we would warmly recommend her to other families as well! First, and most importantly, she is great with our 18 month old. Our daughter is a sensitive child, so it was important for us to find someone who understood how her personality. I have been so impressed by Yaira's approach, and how quickly my daughter got accustomed to her. It's also obvious to us that her learning and development has accelerated since Yaira started watching her. She ensures that the day is filled with a combination of reading, playing, outdoor time and creative activities. 
Secondly, she is a great help to us as parents. She has easily taken any instruction we've given, she is solution oriented, and always curious how she can be more helpful. Also, despite play and fun, the house is always spotless.
